Let 
  
    
      
        X
      
    
    {\displaystyle X}
   be a set of possible `states of the world' or `alternatives'; society wishes to choose some state from 
  
    
      
        X
      
    
    {\displaystyle X}
  . Let 
  
    
      
        I
      
    
    {\displaystyle I}
   be a finite set, representing a collection of people. For each 
  
    
      
        i
        ∈
        I
      
    
    {\displaystyle i\in I}
  , let 
  
    
      
        
          u
          
            i
          
        
        :
        X
        ⟶
        
          R
        
      
    
