   is a `rescaled' utility function which has a minimum value of 0 and a maximum value of 1. The Relative Utilitarian social choice rule selects the element in 
  
    
      
        X
      
    
    {\displaystyle X}
   which maximizes the utilitarian sum

  
    
      
